:R-HSA-112314  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0007268 ;
        rdfs:comment        "The neurotransmitter in the synaptic cleft released by the pre-synaptic neuron binds specific receptors located on the post-synaptic terminal. These receptors are either ion channels or G protein coupled receptors that function to transmit the signals from the post-synaptic membrane to the cell body." ;
        rdfs:label          "Neurotransmitter receptors and postsynaptic signal transmission" ;
        dc:contributor      "Reviewed: Restituito, S, Kavalali, E, 2008-12-02 04:33:19" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Authored: Mahajan, SS, 2008-01-14 16:01:52" ;
